oical Guises of the Man of Feeling -- tNichol Smith Collections in Edinburgh and Oxford -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume presents an array of studies on many aspects of the eighteenth century: on the novel, history, the history of ideas, drama, poetry and sentimentality. The essays are as diverse as ‘Pope’s Essays on Man and the French Enlightenment’ and ‘Of Silk-worms and Farthingales and the Will of God.’ One group is concerned with the works and ideas of Bayle, Alexander Gerard, Diderot, Fuseli, Hawkesworth and Swift among others.The essays are the work of leading scholars for many disciplines and were presented at the Second David Nichol Smith Seminar; together they reflect some of the liveliest and most up-to-date trends in the present reexamination of the period. The book will be invaluable to all students of the literature, thought, and civilisation of the eighteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEighteenth century. 0aEnglish literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aEnglish literaturey18th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 18th Century.2bisacsh1 aAllentuck, Mania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell, A. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrissenden, R.F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarroll, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCashmere, J. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonaldson, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElkner, Brian A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFabian, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/